## Context
Ticket 0026 defines eight citation graph methods. These operate on
citations.csv (the Phase 1 contract file) and produce one value per year.

Reads: refined_works.csv, citations.csv
Writes: content/tables/tab_citation_divergence.csv

## Actions
1. Create `scripts/compute_divergence_citation.py` following script-io
   discipline.
2. Build cumulative citation graph per year using networkx (directed graph,
   nodes = work IDs, edges = citations with year attribute).
3. Implement eight methods, each producing one value per year:
   - G1: PageRank volatility — Kendall tau between PageRank vectors of
     consecutive yearly snapshots.
   - G2: Spectral gap — difference between 1st and 2nd eigenvalue of
     normalized Laplacian of the largest connected component.
   - G3: Bibliographic coupling age shift — median publication year of
     shared references, tracked over time.
   - G4: Cross-tradition citation ratio — define traditions by seed papers
     (use existing tradition detection from the project). Track fraction
     of citations crossing tradition boundaries.
   - G5: Preferential attachment exponent — fit power law to degree
     distribution per yearly snapshot via scipy.optimize.curve_fit.
   - G6: Citation entropy — Shannon entropy of in-degree distribution.
   - G7: Disruption index CD — for papers published in year y, compute
     mean CD_i. Requires: for each paper i, count n_i (citing i not refs),
     n_j (citing both), n_k (citing refs not i).
   - G8: Betweenness centrality — mean betweenness in co-citation network
     per yearly snapshot.
4. Subcorpus: full and core-only.
5. Output: long-format CSV matching 0029 schema.
6. Add Makefile target.

## Complexity notes
- G7 (disruption index) is O(papers × avg_refs × avg_citers) — may need
  batching or caching.
- G2 and G8 are expensive on large graphs — compute on largest connected
  component only, or subsample.
- G4 needs seed papers — check existing tradition detection scripts in
  scripts/archive_traditions/.

## Test
```python
def test_citation_divergence_smoke():
    """Build tiny citation graph, verify G1-G8 produce values."""
```

## Exit criteria
All 8 methods produce yearly series from ~2000 to ~2023. G7 matches
published disruption index properties (mean should decline over time
per Wu et al. 2019).
